Create a File Storage Activation Target

Create an activation target in Data Cloud to publish segments to file storage activation platforms such as Amazon S3, SFTP, Google Cloud Storage (GCS), and Microsoft Azure blob storage.

On the Activation Targets tab, click New.
In File Storage, select an activation platform, and click Next.
Enter a name and an optional description.
For SFTP, GCS, and Microsoft Azure Blob Storage, select the connector.
For S3, enter the bucket and folder details.
Select the data space you want to associate your activation target with.
Click Next.
Enter the activation target details.
IMPORTANT
For S3:
Before you create an activation target, determine your S3 access key and secret key.
Consider enabling server-side encryption for your S3 buckets. Data Cloud supports Amazon S3-managed keys (SSE-S3). Learn more about enabling SSE-S3 encryption.
The S3 credentials must have the following permissions: s3:PutObject, s3:GetObject, s3:ListBucket, s3:DeleteObject, s3:GetBucketLocation.
To delete S3 access or secret keys, you must delete the activation target.
For SFTP, GCS, and Microsoft Azure Blob Storage:
For SFTP, set up at least one of the following options:
A non-root parent directory in the SFTP connector. For more information, see Set Up an SFTP Target Connection.
A child directory in the activation target.
Enable the automatic folder creation option in the activation target.
The child directory must already exist on the SFTP server with Write permission. Data cloud will not create the child directory if it doesn’t exist already.
The child directory name is case-sensitive.
If you select the checkbox ‘Create a folder within child directory’, the files are added to a separate folder. Otherwise, the files are placed in the child directory. The folder name is <SegmentName_ActivationName>. In the folder name, any character (except alphanumeric and underscore) in SegmentName and ActivationName is replaced with a hyphen (-).
For the File Name Type, in the predetermined file name, any character (except alphanumeric and underscore) in SegmentName and ActivationName is replaced with a hyphen (-).
PGP encryption is supported for CSV and JSON file formats, but not Parquet.
By default, the maximum file size for each file exported to the file storage system is 500 MB or 5000 records. If the activation payload is larger than the file size, then the payload is split into multiple files before being exported.
Click Save.

Your activation target is created and these items are added to your file storage activation platform:

A metadata file that describes the segment definition.
Data files that contain the segment members with additional attributes.
A segment data folder to indicate that output files to the folder are complete. If this file is missing, it indicates that either the files are being written or the data was only partially written and it failed.
The output files in CSV format:
Fields can be quoted (for example: value → "value")
If a coma (,) is part of the value, then the field value is quoted (for example: value1,value2 → "value1,value2")
If double quotes are also part of the value, then it includes \ in order to use double quotes (for example: "value1","value2" → "\"value1\",\"value2\"")
Find Segments in File Storage Platforms
After you create and activate segments to file storage platforms, view them in their respective storage locations.
